statewide school closure. Packaged breakfast and lunch is being made available through our

Jenison Public Schools

Kindergarten Screening

March 4 ‚Äì 8, 2019

Jenison Public Schools will be holding Kindergarten Screening the week of Monday, March 4 through Friday, March 8. Jenison Public Schools offers both Transitional Kindergarten and Kindergarten programs for children who will be five years old on or before December 1, 2019.

All students entering either Kindergarten program must be screened prior to placement. You can schedule a screening appointment online by clicking the link on our website at www.JPSonline.org.

Students who are currently enrolled in a JPS Preschool class or in Transitional Kindergarten do not need to schedule a screening appointment nor complete a new online registration form. You will have an opportunity to update your child‚Äôs information online later this summer.

If you have any questions or problems, please contact Lorri at 457-8839 or via email at Lgierman@JPSonline.org.

The Jenison High School Orchestras will be performing with professional rock band, The Outer Vibe. The Outer Vibe has local roots and now resides in Nashville, playing concerts across the country (traveling in their Ford Transit van they call Vanikan Skywalker). This concert will be a Benefit Concert for Hand2Hand which delivers hope to hungry children by mobilizing schools and churches to provide nutritious food over the weekends.
